runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:702:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This is a plausible obstruction route, but in its current form it is structurally under-specified and too eager to turn kinematic closure facts into a dynamical lower bound. Its real strength is not "likely theorem" but "good diagnostic bridge" between definition audit and adversarial construction. If Chain 04 does not first freeze a stable notion of near-closure, this chain is at high risk of producing an impressive ledger with no honest theorem content.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:703:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:22:- There is a hidden assumption that the target circuit graph is already well-defined. But Chain 04 exists precisely because that object may be unstable or circular.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:704:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:35:- The chain quietly assumes finite closure is the relevant object. But near-closure might still be meaningful for packets with small tails rather than strict finite support closure.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:705:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- "Finite-packet non-closure" is not automatically a stronger obstruction. It only kills one model class. The mission target is near-closed Tao-like behavior, not necessarily strict finite packet closure.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:706:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:72:- A positive lower bound that depends strongly on packet size, normalization, or role assignment may not deserve to be called a no-near-closure statement.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:707:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:82:- Dependency inversion: this chain really depends on Chain 04. Without a stable object definition, "leakage" can be tuned by bookkeeping and the whole program becomes selection-biased.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:708:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The weakness is that it tries to turn a hard object-definition and theorem-calibration problem into a search-and-score problem too early. In this mission, that is dangerous. If "near-closed Tao circuit" has not already survived the Chain 04 invariance audit, then Step 1 just invents a proxy and the rest of the chain optimizes that proxy. Then Step 5 overclaims in both directions: a small-packet partial mimic is treated as a clean kill of the firewall idea, while small-family failure is treated as informative obstruction. Neither inference is earned by the current design.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:709:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:20:- The score is vulnerable to representation dependence unless Chain 04 has already frozen the invariant object. Phase conventions, packet regrouping, normalization, and helical bookkeeping can all move a candidate's apparent "likeness" without changing the mathematics.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:710:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The phrase "reduced exact amplitude systems" is the crux. If the candidate is only near-closed, what exactly is being integrated? A truly exact closed packet, or a reduced subsystem obtained by dropping forced modes? If it is the latter, the dynamic test is already compromised.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:711:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:Chain 03 is supposed to coexist with Chain 04, but in practice it tries to bypass it. If the stable definition of "near-closed Tao circuit" is not already fixed, then "Tao-likeness" becomes whatever this chain's score function says it is. That makes the search output hard to trust and hard to compare with the other chains.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:712:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The mission asks about an exact no-near-closed-Tao-circuit statement. A tiny packet that partially mimics pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic does not by itself refute the broader obstruction. It may only show that one naive formulation was too strict.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:713:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:111:That is not obviously the "fastest" route inside a 3-5 exploration mission budget, especially when Chain 04 is supposed to gate the object definition first.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-run-001-judge-02.log:714:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
