runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-001.log:1585:   Yes, the inherited record already supports a sharper discriminator than a generic sparse or multiscale packet idea. It is not a scalar score; it is a feature ledger plus exact interaction template plus admissibility sheet. The discriminator is essentially: a near-isolated five-role delayed-threshold circuit with ordered couplings, fixed packet semantics, fixed canonical presentation, and bounded spectator leakage under exact triadic/Leray dynamics ([exploration 001](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md#L264), [final report](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md#L55), [CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L71)).  
