runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-001.log:1704:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:118:- Even failure could be useful if the output is written modestly as a diagnostic about small exact packets, not as a global theorem surrogate.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-001.log:1705:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
