runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1698:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:7:- Prior work already isolated the three load-bearing exact-NS pressures on the idea: coefficient rigidity, unavoidable spectator couplings, and exact projection/reality bookkeeping.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1699:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:15:Central premise: the smallest exact helical packet capable of mimicking Tao's pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic already fails because the required sign and magnitude hierarchy cannot be realized by one geometry-locked family of triad coefficients.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1700:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:19:Central premise: even if some desired channels can be matched, exact Fourier/helical closure plus mirror-mode bookkeeping forces enough extra interactions that any honest Tao-like subsystem leaks a quantifiable amount of activity outside the five target roles.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1701:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:23:Central premise: the obstruction might be false. The fastest honest kill is to search directly for the best exact NS or helical packet that approximates Tao's logic and see whether it survives exact coupling accounting.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1702:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:27:Central premise: the whole mission may fail at the object-definition level. If every reasonable definition of near-closure is unstable under phase choice, packetization, scaling, or conjugate completion, the right result is a sharp definitional kill rather than a fake theorem program.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1703:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:31:- Chain 01 is algebraic and theorem-facing. It targets incompatible coefficient ratios and sign patterns inside a minimal exact helical model.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1704:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:34:- Chain 04 is meta-definitional. It tests whether the theorem object itself can be made stable enough to support Chains 01-03.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1705:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:38:- Every chain must freeze one exact target object before optimism begins: either a minimal helical packet, a leakage functional, a concrete search family, or a formal definition family.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1706:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:10:- The example families already bias the search toward three particular lenses: graph closure, leakage ratio, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not neutral. `interaction-graph closure` is likely too combinatorial and basis-sensitive; `leakage-ratio closure` quietly presupposes a norm, normalization, and threshold choice; `delayed-threshold behavioral closure` risks hard-coding Tao's averaged mechanism back into the object.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1707:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:11:- The step asks for support, normalization, time window, and spectator size, but it omits several quantities that exact NS actually cares about: phase information, helical sign pattern, amplitude hierarchy, and whether "support" means single modes, conjugate pairs, or packets. That omission matters because triadic forcing depends on more than a support graph.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1708:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:13:- The kill condition is too weak. A formulaic but ad hoc definition can survive this step even if it is just a dressed-up paraphrase with tuned thresholds.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1709:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:21:- The chain mixes true symmetries with bookkeeping conventions. `rescaling` is not a harmless cosmetic move unless the full NS scaling, including time and viscosity normalization, is specified. `conjugate completion` is not cosmetic either; for real-valued velocity fields it changes what the packet literally is. `packet regrouping` can change nonlinear bookkeeping in a way that is mathematically substantive, not merely presentational.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1710:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:24:- `helical basis choice` is especially slippery here. If the definition is attached to exact mode interactions, basis dependence may reflect a bad representation choice that should be fixed by canonicalization, not a reason to kill the object entirely.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1711:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:25:- The stable/unstable/conditionally stable table is too coarse. Many workable mathematical objects are only stable after choosing a canonical representation. That is not ideal, but it is not obviously fatal for theorem use.
runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-explorer-002.log:1712:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:29:## Step 3 - Audit dynamical testability on small exact packets
