+# Helical Signs Amplitude Normalization And Phase Anchor Belong To The Frozen Packet Sheet
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` sign relevance with `INFERRED` packet-sheet policy
+
+Later exact-support candidates should not leave packet-sheet data implicit.
+Each promoted packet family should declare:
+
+- one helical sign sheet for every packet role
+- one amplitude normalization anchor
+- one phase anchor or equivalent canonical gauge
+
+On this record, sign data is already part of the exact mismatch the branch is
+trying to test, and phase bookkeeping is named as part of the missing object
+discipline. Freezing these choices up front prevents later candidate
+comparisons from drifting through hidden rescalings or phase-sheet changes.
+
+Filed from:
